{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_0","type":"agent_message","text":"final_filename: p1.cir\n\nObjective: Create a single-stage NMOS common-source voltage amplifier using a resistive load, with input node `Vin` and output node `Vout`.\n\nTopology: Use one NMOS transistor in common-source configuration. Connect the NMOS drain to `Vout`, source to ground, bulk tied to source/ground, and gate driven by `Vin`. Connect a resistive load `R` from `VDD` to `Vout`.\n\nRequired devices:\n- Independent DC supply `VDD` from node `VDD` to ground, value 5 V.\n- Independent input source driving node `Vin`, with DC bias at or above 1.2 V and small-signal AC magnitude for gain analysis.\n- One NMOS transistor using model `NMOS`, with W=50u and L=1u.\n- One resistor load `R` from `VDD` to `Vout`, value between 10k and 100k ohm. Use a nominal value such as 50k unless otherwise optimized.\n\nBiasing assumptions:\n- Bias `Vin` with DC value around 1.2 V to satisfy the requirement that the NMOS gate is at least 1.2 V.\n- With source at ground and gate at 1.2 V, expected overdrive is about 0.5 V using Vth=0.7 V.\n- Choose the load resistor so the DC drain voltage at `Vout` remains high enough for saturation: approximately `Vout >= Vin - Vth`, so target `Vout > 0.5 V`.\n- NMOS bulk must be tied to source/ground.\n\nAnalyses:\n- Include `.op` to verify DC operating point, drain voltage, current, and saturation condition.\n- Include `.ac dec 20 1 1e9` to evaluate small-signal voltage gain from `Vin` to `Vout`.\n\nOutput constraints:\n- The final SPICE netlist must be saved as `p1.cir`.\n- Nodes `Vin` and `Vout` must appear exactly with those names.\n- `Vin` must be electrically driven by an explicit independent voltage source.\n- `Vout` must be the NMOS drain and amplifier output node.\n- Use explicit MOSFET model definitions matching: NMOS Vth=0.7 V, kp=100u, W=50u, L=1u."}}
